# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: Demonarc4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah sat down on the heaped up pile of hay."
    new "Sarah sat down on the heaped up pile of hay."

    old "Outside, the cold winds howled."
    new "Outside, the cold winds howled."

    old "Sarah could feel the cold wind cut through the gaps and holes of the old ruined castle."
    new "Sarah could feel the cold wind cut through the gaps and holes of the old ruined castle."

    old "Outside was probably worse, but inside was hardly better."
    new "Outside was probably worse, but inside was hardly better."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, she watched as Dalia climbed into her bed."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, she watched as Dalia climbed into her bed."

    old "A real bed. An actual bed."
    new "A real bed. An actual bed."

    old "And instead, she was forced to sit and sleep on a pil of hay, as if she were some farm animal."
    new "And instead, she was forced to sit and sleep on a pil of hay, as if she were some farm animal."

    old "A spike of resentment build in her."
    new "A spike of resentment build in her."

    old "What made that girl think she was any better than her?"
    new "What made that girl think she was any better than her?"

    old "But it faded away just as quickly."
    new "But it faded away just as quickly."

    old "None of it was Dalia's fault."
    new "None of it was Dalia's fault."

    old "If anything, this was likely just another game, played on them by the Master."
    new "If anything, this was likely just another game, played on them by the Master."

    old "Pitching them against one another over some trivial thing."
    new "Pitching them against one another over some trivial thing."

    old "Driving a wedge between them."
    new "Driving a wedge between them."

    old "Sarah crawled up into a corner of her hay bed."
    new "Sarah crawled up into a corner of her hay bed."

    old "She did her best to make it feel comfortable, knowing that it never would."
    new "She did her best to make it feel comfortable, knowing that it never would."

    old "Looking over at Dalia, she contemplated asking to join her."
    new "Looking over at Dalia, she contemplated asking to join her."

    old "Simply the idea of her body heat was enough source of comfort."
    new "Simply the idea of her body heat was enough source of comfort."

    old "Or the touch of someone that was as close as friend in this wretched place."
    new "Or the touch of someone that was as close as friend in this wretched place."

    old "But she couldn't ask it."
    new "But she couldn't ask it."

    old "Not after everything that had happened today."
    new "Not after everything that had happened today."

    old "Sarah rolled back to the corner of the hay bed."
    new "Sarah rolled back to the corner of the hay bed."

    old "The coarse fabric, stabbing into her skin."
    new "The coarse fabric, stabbing into her skin."

    old "She shivered as the cold winds raged through the cracks of the old broken fort."
    new "She shivered as the cold winds raged through the cracks of the old broken fort."

    old "Sarah never asked Dalia to join her in the bed."
    new "Sarah never asked Dalia to join her in the bed."

    old "She held out hope that Dalia might invite her instead."
    new "She held out hope that Dalia might invite her instead."

    old "But that hope proved likewise idle."
    new "But that hope proved likewise idle."

    old "Instead, she slept alone, and had never felt more alone in all her life."
    new "Instead, she slept alone, and had never felt more alone in all her life."

    old "Would you mind if I...slept in your bed with you?"
    new "Would you mind if I...slept in your bed with you?"

    old "Sarah watched the girl sit upright."
    new "Sarah watched the girl sit upright."

    old "No reason for you to sleep on that hay. There is plenty of space in the bed for both of us."
    new "No reason for you to sleep on that hay. There is plenty of space in the bed for both of us."

    old "Sarah got up and walked towards the bed."
    new "Sarah got up and walked towards the bed."

    old "Dalia pulled back the covers and Sarah slipped into the bed."
    new "Dalia pulled back the covers and Sarah slipped into the bed."

    old "When Dalia pulled the covers back over the both of them, Sarah instantly felt the warmth."
    new "When Dalia pulled the covers back over the both of them, Sarah instantly felt the warmth."

    old "Outside, she could still hear the roaring wind, pounding against the frail castle."
    new "Outside, she could still hear the roaring wind, pounding against the frail castle."

    old "But here, underneath the covers, it felt warm. Safe, almost."
    new "But here, underneath the covers, it felt warm. Safe, almost."

    old "Sarah rolled to face Dalia and found the girl already facing her."
    new "Sarah rolled to face Dalia and found the girl already facing her."

    old "She had been sitting in the dark long enough that her sight had grown used to it."
    new "She had been sitting in the dark long enough that her sight had grown used to it."

    old "Sarah spoke softly, as if someone might be listening."
    new "Sarah spoke softly, as if someone might be listening."

    old "Perhaps they were."
    new "Perhaps they were."

    old "When I first got here, the thing I wanted most of all was someone else here..."
    new "When I first got here, the thing I wanted most of all was someone else here..."

    old "You wanted someone else to be in this hell?"
    new "You wanted someone else to be in this hell?"

    old "No, not literally. But just the idea...that I would have someone that I could be with."
    new "No, not literally. But just the idea...that I would have someone that I could be with."

    old "Someone other than Him."
    new "Someone other than Him."

    old "I understand. I'm also happy that I'm not alone."
    new "I understand. I'm also happy that I'm not alone."

    old "That much was the truth."
    new "That much was the truth."

    old "Thank you, by the way."
    new "Thank you, by the way."

    old "For not fighting the Master."
    new "For not fighting the Master."

    old "I mean...I know it's not easy..."
    new "I mean...I know it's not easy..."

    old "Sarah reached out and touched Dalia."
    new "Sarah reached out and touched Dalia."

    old "With the tip of her fingers, she felt her naked skin."
    new "With the tip of her fingers, she felt her naked skin."

    old "Dalia was wearing her outfit, but she might as well be nude."
    new "Dalia was wearing her outfit, but she might as well be nude."

    old "When I heard he would punish you if I defied him, I knew I wouldn't let that happen."
    new "When I heard he would punish you if I defied him, I knew I wouldn't let that happen."

    old "Taking the punishment myself is one thing, but I couldn't make you suffer like that."
    new "Taking the punishment myself is one thing, but I couldn't make you suffer like that."

    old "Thank you. You really are a good friend."
    new "Thank you. You really are a good friend."

    old "Friend. Was that what they were."
    new "Friend. Was that what they were."

    old "Some part of her wanted to desperately trust this girl. Some other part of her warned her against it."
    new "Some part of her wanted to desperately trust this girl. Some other part of her warned her against it."

    old "But in the midst of all that loneliness, it was a tempting idea. A friend."
    new "But in the midst of all that loneliness, it was a tempting idea. A friend."

    old "Now, let's try to get some sleep."
    new "Now, let's try to get some sleep."

    old "Another long day tomorrow."
    new "Another long day tomorrow."

    old "Sarah softly nodded, and before long, the two of them were fast asleep."
    new "Sarah softly nodded, and before long, the two of them were fast asleep."

